com.android.os.HttpClient - Deprecated in approx. Android 6.0.
Not to used anymore. Building a complete web browser 
on the device. Made by google and did not have any community process
for its improvements. Open Source.

java.net.HttpURLConnection - Was developed by Oracle(formerly Sun Microsystem). Recommended ways of doing network operations on device.
Open For development.
Link: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/net/HttpURLConnection.html

okhttp - Another famous http client build for Java. Built by engineers at Square. Becoming a goto choice for developers for implementation of networking  in the app. Open Source.
 Link: https://square.github.io/okhttp/


Retrofit: It is a wrapper over SOME HTTP CLIENT.
- Built by Square Inc.
- Open Source
- Has http client
- Has configurable JSON parser
- Has configurable JSON mapper
- Support RxJava
- Link https://square.github.io/retrofit/
- Much more.

Volley: It is a wrapper over HttpClient(not sure).
- Built by Google.
- Open Source
- Has http client
- Has configurable JSON parser
- Support RxJava
- Link https://developer.android.com/training/volley/simple
- Much more.

is Volly a type of http client?


